OL,3,CMore than 2,000 prosecuted in
OL,4,Cshoplifting crackdown
OL,6,FDeborah Leeson said: "When we report
OL,7,Fincidents now, they are being dealt
OL,8,Fwith and if it is the prolific
OL,9,Fshoplifters that we get, then the
OL,10,Fconsequences are getting a lot tougher
OL,11,Ffor them."
OL,13,FLancashire Police Chief Inspector
OL,14,FChris Abbott said:"We have seen over
OL,15,F2,100 prosecutions, we have seen over
OL,16,F630 arrests, over 25 civil orders
OL,17,Fagainst our most prolific shoplifters,
OL,18,Fand that may exclude them from
OL,19,Fentering certain areas of Lancashire
OL,20,Fand shops."
